{"TopicId":222135,"ForumId":126,"TopicTitle":"Docking and RCS - what am I missing?","CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-26T23:55:42Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-26T23:55:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst docking attempt since For Science! (and maybe KSP2) came out.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI got my crafts close, hit DEL for docking mode, and tried to use the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters to bring the crafts together.\u00A0 However, with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E enabled and my engine disabled - I can\u0027t get forward thrust.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom what \u0027muscle memory\u0027 tells me of the long ago time I played KSP - in Docking Mode the Shift and CNTRL keys should give me forward and rearward puffs.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNothing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI ended up having to restart the engine and turn down thrust a lot to give me closing speed.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClearly I\u0027m missing something; shouldn\u0027t KSP2 give me \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E control in Docking mode via WASD \u002B CNTRL \u0026amp; Shift?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis damn docking, FWIW, was both successful and played out in real time; took me 45 minutes from when I got the craft w/in 75m of each other.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-27T01:03:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nH is forwards, N is backwards.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Unless \u0022docking mode\u0022 is drastically different. I still haven\u0027t tried it in either game.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-12-27T01:04:49Z\u0022 title=\u002212/27/2023 01:04  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Dec 27\u0022\u003EDecember 27, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by HebaruSan\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-28T02:53:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWorst of all.. the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E puffs are very unstable, they never stop adjusting.I think the control algorithm is bad. It makes docking very difficult.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-28T03:09:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve not docked or used \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E yet in ksp2. Do you not have the ability to disable using them for roll/pitch/yaw?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat was step 1 in KSP. I even had a Module Manager config that set them that way by default.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"18Watt","CreatedById":198538,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-28T03:10:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224352997\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022222135\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703732006\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWorst of all.. the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E puffs are very unstable, they never stop adjusting.I think the control algorithm is bad. It makes docking very difficult.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had the same issue in KSP1. \u00A0Currently, in KSP2, the solution (for me) is identical. \u00A0I turn off Pitch Roll Yaw on all \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters, and only use them for translations (HNIJKL). \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224352999\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022222135\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703732983\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you not have the ability to disable using them for roll/pitch/yaw?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, you can still do that, and yes it\u0027s still a good idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224352999\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022222135\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703732983\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat was step 1 in KSP.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill step 1 in KSP2..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-28T13:52:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224353000\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022222135\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703733016\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022198538\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u002218Watt\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, 18Watt said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI turn off Pitch Roll Yaw on all \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters, and only use them for translations (HNIJKL). \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAha.. well.. I learn something new every day.. I\u0027ll try that. But the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E / stability / control algo is still jank.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-28T14:01:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224352460\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022222135\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703634942\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/26/2023 at 6:55 PM, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI got my crafts close, hit DEL for docking mode, and tried to use the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters to bring the crafts together\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI find it easier to skip docking mode altogether and just use IJKL for translation (HN fwd/bck). If you do need to fix your orientation it\u0027s easier to do without having to switch back and forth to docking mode. And as mentioned in nearly all the responses; turn off yaw/pitch/roll for the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat should make it easier. Good luck!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-28T14:05:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224353000\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022222135\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703733016\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022198538\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u002218Watt\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, 18Watt said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had the same issue in KSP1. \u00A0Currently, in KSP2, the solution (for me) is identical. \u00A0I turn off Pitch Roll Yaw on all \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters, and only use them for translations (HNIJKL). \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, you can still do that, and yes it\u0027s still a good idea.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill step 1 in KSP2..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... And yet they don\u0027t tell me how.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSMH.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is a harsh forum.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-28T14:15:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224353098\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022222135\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703772331\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... And yet they don\u0027t tell me how.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSMH.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is a harsh forum.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn KSP1 you have to activae tweakables in the settings\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn KSP2 it\u0027s in the part manager, ut you might have to twirl/unfold that option open to see the 6 axis options for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters. When [;aced with symmetry you only have to edit one of them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"18Watt","CreatedById":198538,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-28T17:45:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224353098\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022222135\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703772331\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154477\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022JoeSchmuckatelli\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, JoeSchmuckatelli said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n... And yet they don\u0027t tell me how.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry Joe, I made a bad assumption. \u00A0My bad.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/78303-kerbart/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002278303\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/78303-kerbart/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Kerbart\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0said, if you placed the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters via symmetry, you only need to deactivate pitch roll yaw on one of them. \u00A0Not sure if that works in flight, and I always check each one anyway, just because.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-28T17:59:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224353179\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022222135\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221703785502\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022198538\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u002218Watt\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, 18Watt said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Not sure if that works in flight, and I always check each one anyway, just because.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes it does. I know because I haven\u0027t found a way to remove parts from symmetry in flight (if you adjust spring strength individually on landing legs you can straighten out a craft landed on a slope in KSP1, but I haven\u0027t found out how to do it in KSP2)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}